00:00:56.290 --> 00:01:01.260
So, accounts in Ad Proto, they have users,

00:01:01.270 --> 00:01:05.260
and users I kind of call decentralized identifiers.

00:01:05.270 --> 00:01:13.320
And each decentralized identifier basically has cryptographic keys attached to it

00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:13.680
.

00:01:13.690 --> 00:01:21.360
And these cryptographic keys control what is authorized by each user

00:01:21.370 --> 00:01:26.000
to be posted or done in their name.

00:01:26.010 --> 00:01:30.390
There are different kinds of deeds, and we will talk about

00:01:30.390 --> 00:01:33.640
a couple of them later and what guarantees each of them gives

00:01:33.640 --> 00:01:33.980
you.

00:01:34.010 --> 00:01:37.560
But what you have to know is just this fact.

00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:43.560
Each user has this decentralized identifier attached to them, and each

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:46.990
of them has what's called a repo sign-in key

00:01:46.990 --> 00:01:47.220
.

00:01:47.230 --> 00:01:52.510
This repo sign-in key basically authenticates every operation that

00:01:52.510 --> 00:01:53.790
your deeds make.

00:01:55.310 --> 00:01:57.040
So, that means posting.

00:01:57.050 --> 00:01:58.910
That means doing likes.

00:01:58.930 --> 00:02:04.610
That means doing everything else that other apps do on your account

00:02:04.610 --> 00:02:04.990
.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:06.660
So, it could be anything.

00:02:06.670 --> 00:02:09.600
What is the guarantee that you get?

00:02:09.610 --> 00:02:10.780
This is a sign-in key.

00:02:10.790 --> 00:02:12.590
This is a digital signature.

00:02:12.610 --> 00:02:17.870
So, the guarantee that you get is this deed agreed for

00:02:17.870 --> 00:02:22.290
this record to be published or for this operation to be performed

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:22.520
.

00:02:22.530 --> 00:02:26.050
But that's kind of what you get, which is already

00:02:26.050 --> 00:02:27.220
very powerful.

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:30.680
You already get end-to-end verifiability.

00:02:30.690 --> 00:02:35.970
So, a deed that is published on, that is used

00:02:35.970 --> 00:02:38.640
on the network has these keys.

00:02:38.650 --> 00:02:42.500
So, whenever you want to verify a post is valid,

00:02:42.530 --> 00:02:44.280
you can go to the post.

00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:46.130
You can see which deed posted it.

00:02:46.150 --> 00:02:50.330
You can then take what's called a deed document, which

00:02:50.330 --> 00:02:52.730
then lists what cryptographic keys it has.

00:02:52.750 --> 00:02:54.590
You can get those keys.

00:02:54.610 --> 00:02:57.720
You can verify the signature on something.

00:02:57.730 --> 00:03:00.080
Let's call it verify the signature on the record.

00:03:00.090 --> 00:03:01.960
And pretty much done.

00:03:01.990 --> 00:03:05.500
So, this is a very nice property of AdProto

00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:06.280
in general.

00:03:06.290 --> 00:03:12.720
But what if you wanted a bit more from this guarantee?

00:03:12.730 --> 00:03:16.280
So, not only this deed authorized is supposed to be published

00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:19.110
, what if you want more?

00:03:19.630 --> 00:03:23.340
So, what if you want to have some logic attached to

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:26.040
each operation that is performed in your name?

00:03:26.050 --> 00:03:30.950
An example, like a few examples, would be, let

00:03:30.950 --> 00:03:35.880
's say that each post that is published in your account,

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:38.550
you want it to be verified by some LLM that

00:03:38.550 --> 00:03:42.630
runs some analysis and check that it's like a non-

00:03:42.630 --> 00:03:45.750
toxic post that runs an LLM that runs on

00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:46.260
your computer.

00:03:47.350 --> 00:03:51.970
What if we want to get a guarantee that the images that

00:03:51.970 --> 00:03:56.030
you're posting or that someone else is posting are coming from

00:03:56.030 --> 00:03:57.660
a trusted source?

00:03:57.660 --> 00:04:00.420
So, for example, you have cameras today that have digital

00:04:00.420 --> 00:04:01.400
signatures on them.

00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:04.070
So, you can verify that these are images that have not

00:04:04.070 --> 00:04:05.430
been tampered with, for example.

00:04:06.930 --> 00:04:09.640
What about a kind of multi-signature accounts or

00:04:09.640 --> 00:04:11.490
an organizational account?

00:04:11.510 --> 00:04:16.120
Each post has to be authorized by two out of three people

00:04:16.130 --> 00:04:24.800
so that if you want some more trust

00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:27.380
in those posts, you can add that kind of logic.

00:04:27.390 --> 00:04:30.940
Or maybe you want some verified bot accounts.

00:04:31.070 --> 00:04:34.380
So, that, for example, could be a bot account

00:04:34.390 --> 00:04:38.330
that runs with a given system prompt because we don't want

